attachments.title: Google confirms next Android version will use Oracle’s open-source OpenJDK for Java APIs
attachments.text: Google is replacing its implementation of the Java application programming interfaces (APIs) in Android with OpenJDK, the open source version of Oracle's Java Development Kit (JDK). The news first came by a "mysterious Android codebase commit" from last month submitted to Hacker News. Google confirmed to VentureBeat that Android N will rely on an OpenJDK implementation, rather Android's own implementation of the Java APIs.
